data.content:
Created four files under `Components/`:

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `Order.cs` | Models (`ShippingInfo`, `PaymentInfo`, `Order`) |
| `CheckoutWizard.razor` | Manages step state and the `Order` instance. Exposes `OnOrderPlaced` (`EventCallback<Order>`) to the parent. |
| `ShippingStep.razor` | Binds to `ShippingInfo` fields. Blocks "Next" if `Name` or `Address` is empty, showing a validation message. |
| `PaymentStep.razor` | Binds to `PaymentInfo` fields. "Back" returns to shipping; "Place Order" fires `OnPlaceOrder`. |

**Usage from a parent component:**

```razor
<CheckoutWizard OnOrderPlaced="HandleOrder" />

@code {
    private async Task HandleOrder(Order order)
    {
        // order.Shipping and order.Payment are populated
    }
}
```

The `Order` object flows through the wizard by reference — both steps mutate the same instance owned by `CheckoutWizard`, so the parent receives the fully completed order.
